article.headline: Siena 69, Fairfield 64
article.story: BRIDGEPORT, Conn. (AP) -- Michael Haddix scored 19 points and Alex Franklin added 13 as Siena rallied from a 10-point deficit in the final 7:34 to beat Fairfield 69-64 on Wednesday. The Stags (11-17, 9-7 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference) led 58-48 after a 3-pointer by Danny Oglesby, but went scoreless for the next 4 1/2 minutes. Siena (16-10, 11-5) ended the game with a 21-6 run. Franklin scored eight points in that spurt as the Saints won their fifth straight Tay Fisher added 11 points and Kenny Hasbrouck had 10 for Siena. Fairfield, losing for just the second time in its last 10 games, was paced by Jonathan Hans 15 points. Anthony Johnson had 14 and Michael Van Schaick had 10 for the Stags. Siena had 30 points off 21 Farifield turnovers. The game was played despite a major winter storm that swept across the Northeast.
